Determined to eradicate smuggling, wrong declaration of cargo and other anti-economic vices, the Nigeria Customs Service and its counterpart in Benin Republic, have today entered into a bilateral connectivity agreement. The agreement, reached just few minutes ago at the Nigeria Customs/ Benin Republic Stakeholders meeting on Connectivity, presently ongoing inside the ECOWAS BUILDING, Seme border, is aimed at facilitating trade between both countries. The agreement will be signed at a later date this month by both countries. Details shortlyâ€¦   